'''Dr. T's Music Software''' was a software company based in [[Massachusetts]]. Development was started in 1984 by Emile Tobenfeld.<ref name="Start20">{{cite magazine|url=https://archive.org/stream/STart-Magazine-Issue-20#page/n47/mode/2up/|title=The Doctor Is In|magazine=STart|date=April 1989|pages=46-7|volume=3|number=9|issn=08896216|oclc=14047163}}</ref> The company operated until the mid-1990s, and developed [[music software]] for the [[Commodore 64]], [[Commodore 128]], [[Commodore Amiga]], [[Macintosh]] and mainly the [[Atari ST]].<ref name="Start20" />
